node.text:
“Your task is not to seek for love, but merely to seek and find all the barriers within yourself that you have built against it.” - Rumi

Rumi Dome at #CalEarthInstitute, constructed 1993-1994

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cal-Earth Institute in Cal-Earth Institute with @stephhimango. May be an image of indoor.

node.text: One of our favorite #CalEarth interiors. Earth One is equipped with air conditioning, a fireplace, full kitchen and various other standard amenities. It demonstrates the ways in which our home’s everyday pleasures can be integrated into #SuperAdobe architecture.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cal-Earth Institute on August 18, 2021 tagging @vir_sanchis. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: CalEarth alumna @vir_sanchis shows us it’s easy being green with her stunning private home in Praia do Rosa, Brazil. Constructed in 2004 using SuperAdobe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cal-Earth Institute on August 17, 2021. May be an image of sky.

node.text: Stunning from sunset to sunrise. An early photo of Bonita Domes in Joshua Tree (originally owned, designed, and built by Lisa Starr who used the space as her home studio and retreat before selling in 2020). Guests who visit can enjoy the domes’ shared resilience and beauty with the desert landscape that surrounds it.
